We have many implementations of python programming in different languages. Some are :

  1.  CPython
  2.  Jython
  3.  PyPy
  4.  IronPython
  5.  Stackless Python
  6.  MicroPython

Different implementations mean different versions of Python made for different purposes and platforms.

Implementation	  |  Easy Explanation

CPython       	  |  The official and most common version of Python written in C language.
Jython	          |  Python version that runs on Java platform (JVM).
PyPy	          |  Faster version of Python that improves execution speed.
IronPython	      |  Python version made for the .NET framework.
Stackless Python  |  Python designed for better multitasking and handling many tasks together.
MicroPython	      |  Small and lightweight Python used in microcontrollers and embedded devices.

In Short :-

CPython → Normal Python
Jython → Python + Java
PyPy → Fast Python
IronPython → Python + .NET
Stackless Python → Better multitasking Python
MicroPython → Python for small devices and hardware
